    "In the healthcare domain, a comparison of statistical, neural, and ensemble methods for predicting patients' weekly average spending on pain medications has demonstrated that ensemble models outperform individual approaches.",
    "Overall, the literature indicates the field of time series forecasting is shifting towards the adoption of machine learning or deep learning methods, showcasing competitive performance in various domains.",
    "While statistical models remain popular for their simplicity, the advancements in neural network architectures offer promising alternatives for efficient forecasting.Handling extreme values in time series is often overlooked by deep learning and machine learning models.",
    "The paper [26] highlights the challenges of diverse numerical routines, aiming to compare and discuss practical issues often overlooked in theoretical discussions.",
    "This oversight primarily arises from the significant imbalance in the data, where extreme events are rare compared to more common occurrences."
